r at Morton than at Boulby. Moreover, the Hartlepool power plant has two\ncores whereas the Perry plant has a single core. The Boulby site, therefore,\noffers an opportunity for demonstrating remote reactor monitoring under more\nstringent conditions than does the Morton site.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 5 Nov 2016 00:19:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-11-08"}
